; Behavioral checks for the family-history extraction — multi-hop
; questions the notes only imply. Solutions are written exactly as
; `cave query` prints them; the harness self-checks that the golden
; satisfies every expectation before any agent run is scored.

?a PARENT-OF+ me
  ?a = anna
  ?a = helena
  ?a = helena/father
  ?a = jan
  ?a = maria

; same stored rows, read from the other end (PARENT-OF REVERSE CHILD-OF)
?d CHILD-OF+ helena
  ?d = anna
  ?d = jan
  ?d = maria
  ?d = me

; the believed birth year — the cousin's 40% claim must not pass the filter
jan HAS birth-year: ?y
  WHERE conf >= 0.6
  ?y = 1932

; the DNA result must be recorded (no expectations = the pattern must hold)
piotr/branch IS related-family

; and nobody is recorded as my child
me PARENT-OF ?child
  none
